body:
This resourcepack copies vanilla but as a songpack for Reactive Music.
This pack can be helpful as a template for other songpacks based on vanilla music or if you want to change music to vanilla without disabling the mod.
# How to install the resource pack
- Download [Reactive Music mod](https://modrinth.com/mod/reactive-music) ([unofficial 26.1 port](https://github.com/KevBelisle/ReactiveMusic-Cont/releases))
- Download this resource pack
- Open Reactive Music settings (use [Mod Menu](https://modrinth.com/mod/modmenu) or `/reactivemusic` command in the world)
- Choose **Reactive Music: OFF** in the list
  - There are a few different special versions available that you can choose if you want



# Different versions in one file
### There are different versions of the songpack all stored inside the pack:
- Available in Reactive Music menu by default:
  - latest version preset;
  - Alpha 1.2.0 / Beta 1.7.3 preset;
  - C418 songs only preset;
  - Old main menu songs only preset;
  - Creative mode exclusive songs only;
  - Creative mode presets based on multiple presets:
    - latest version;
    - Alpha 1.2.0 / Beta 1.7.3;
    - C418 songs only;
- Available only by unarchiving the songpack:
  - presets for every Minecraft version where new music were added.

<details>
<summary>How to choose the version of the pack:</summary>

- Some of the main presets are already available in Reactive Music menu. Just select it if it's there;
- If you want something more specific, unarchive the songpack;
- Copy yaml file of the version you want to use from _songpack-versions_ folder;
- Past it in songpack root folder (the folder where _README.txt_ is);
- Preferably archive the pack again;
- Select this version in Reactive Music menu.

</details>
